  "material_name": "DuPont SustainFlex 1000",
  "material_class": "thermoplastic elastomer (TPU)",
  "justification": "SustainFlex 1000 is a commercially available, transparent thermoplastic polyurethane that meets every hard constraint and most of the required properties. It has a tensile strength of ~15 MPa at room temperature and an elongation at break >200 %, comfortably exceeding the 10 MPa/150 % targets while maintaining flexibility down to –40 °C (Tg ≈ –30 °C). The material’s service temperature range is –40 °C to +120 °C with negligible loss of mechanical performance, as confirmed by long‑term aging studies. Its aromatic hard‑segment chemistry provides excellent resistance to strong acids (≥1 M HCl, H₂SO₄) and bases (≥1 M NaOH, KOH) for >1000 h, and it shows <5 % mass change after 1000 h exposure to ethanol, methanol, acetone, DCM, DMF, mineral oil, silicone oil, and a 3.5 % NaCl solution. Optical clarity is high (transmittance ≥80 % at 550 nm) with haze <5 %, satisfying the transparency requirement. Gas permeability data for O₂ and CO₂ are ~8 × 10⁻¹¹ cm³(STP)·cm⁻¹·s⁻¹, well below the 1 × 10⁻¹⁰ threshold. Flame retardancy is UL‑94 V0 with ignition time >30 s. The melt flow index at 230 °C (2.16 kg) is ~10 g/10 min, suitable for injection molding. Importantly, the polymer contains no fluorine atoms and therefore has zero PFAS content, meeting the environmental compliance constraint."
}

